eciseness of words as well as their ambiguity, their capacity to represent as well as their propensity to distort. The author examines Marías's constant awareness of how languagecan be used to construct stories as the foundation for engaging the world as well as for imagining it. The nature of Marías's storytelling, and the way in which he imagines, form the principal focus of this Companion. David K. Herzberger is Professor and Chair of the Department of Hispanic Studies at the University of California, Riverside.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 4aHispanic Studies. 4aModern Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Spanish & Portuguese.2bisacsh  aFiction.  aJavier Marías.  aLanguage.  aLiterary Formation.  aSpanish Writer.  aSpanish literature.  aSpanish writer.  aStorytelling.  aintellectual formation.  alanguage precision.  aliterary analysis.  aliterary fictions.  aliterary perspective.  anovels.  ashort stories.  astorytelling.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846159909423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846159909/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles